{"type":"message","id":"d357e9b8","parentId":"6592d3b9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:52:57.905Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_36d90687-1ae0-4ed1-9397-b90e0734981e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-24\n\n## Sprint Check-ins\n\n### 07:02 UTC (09:02 SAST) — Progress Report Cron\n- Progress report cron (32662c28) fired — intended for Tiny but Tiny is active in TUI session\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0) was active ~08:00 SAST with active NurseSphere/Post 002 discussion\n- Tiny was asking about context recovery options in TUI session\n- Main session (this one) has received no direct messages from Tiny since Mar 22 evening\n- Cron delivery mode=none means no push to external channel — this is correct behavior\n- Progress report not relayed to main chat since user is not present here\n\n**TUI session activity (from sessions_list):**\n- agent:main:tui-993acfe0 last active: ~08:00 SAST\n- Topic: NurseSphere context gap, Post 002 discussion, context overflow recovery options\n- Assistant admitted to jumping ahead on drafts 001-010 without review step\n- Tiny was pushing back on process violations\n\n**Morning routine (0162db2e) status:**\n- Should have fired at 06:30 SAST (04:30 UTC)\n- Firing evidence in memory file (07:00 SAST entry exists) — cron worked today\n- Tiny already active in TUI by 08:00 SAST — may have been contacted via TUI directly\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- Sprint crons firing normally (06:50, 06:53, 07:00)\n- morning-routine (0162db2e) still overdue — nextRunAt shows 04:30 UTC (stale), hasn't fired today\n- User silent since Mar 22 evening (~47h)\n- All pending items unchanged from Mar 22 session\n\n**Sprint pending (unchanged since Mar 22):**\n| # | Task | Status |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered Mar 22, awaiting review |\n| 2 | LinkedIn re-scrape (78 posts) | Direction pending |\n| 3 | Writing lesson | Pending |\n| 4 | Crisis by Design series | Deferred |\n\n### 06:53 UTC (08:53 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in fires — cron alive again after ~6h gap\n- User still silent since Mar 22 evening (~46h)\n- All pending items unchanged (X thread review, LinkedIn direction, writing lesson)\n\n### 06:40 UTC (08:40 SAST)\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- Gateway OK (pid 65120, RPC probe ok)\n- Sprint crons still overdue — lastRunAt values ~6h old, no new fires since wake\n- Cron daemon likely needs explicit restart to clear stale nextRunAtMs backlog\n- User still silent (no messages since Mar 22 evening)\n- All pending items unchanged\n- Investigation deferred until user returns or next manual check\n\n### 00:10 UTC (02:10 SAST)\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- User silent — likely sleeping (2:10am SAST)\n- Sprint reminders still duplicating every ~10 min instead of 30\n- No blockers; all items unchanged from Mar 22\n\n## Day State (2026-03-23 end-of-day summary)\n\n**Sprint status:**\n| # | Task | Status |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | Nava RAG (crawl → synthesis → full RAG) | ✅ Complete |\n| 2 | X Thread for Post 001 | ⏳ Draft delivered Mar 22, awaiting review |\n| 3 | LinkedIn re-scrape (78 posts) | ⏳ Direction pending |\n| 4 | Writing lesson | ⏳ Pending |\n| 5 | Crisis by Design series | ⏳ Deferred |\n\n**Key events from Mar 23:**\n- Morning session (06:50–07:00 SAST): Corpus review, Yosef exclusion confirmed as user directive, hallucination pattern discussed (three errors in ~3 hours: Yosef hallucination, screenshot folder error, blog corpus non-existence claim)\n- Critical admission: Told Tiny the blog corpus doesn't exist — it actually DOES exist in `rag/clean_txt/` (22 navahc.com articles)\n- Resource map written to MEMORY.md (backup locations, corpus locations, skills table)\n- Sprint reminders started duplicating — needs investigation when Tiny returns\n\n**Reminder storm:** Sprint reminders firing every ~10 min instead of 30 — multiple backlogged events from the cron system. No user action needed.\n\n**Pending decisions for Tiny:**\n1. Whether to adjust reminder interval\n2. Whether to proceed with LinkedIn full extraction\n3. When to review X thread draft\n4. Writing lesson timing\n\n## X Posts Session (08:43 SAST)\n\n**Task:** X Posts 001-006 minimum, then writing lesson\n**Post 001 topic:** Fee alignment (back-loaded fee model)\n**Posts 002-006:** Cost iceberg, LTC, transaction vs relationship, perfect on paper, false finish line\n\n**Corpus quality flag (noted for Tiny):**\n- 9 articles in rag/clean_txt/ do NOT have \"By Tiny Manyonga\" byline\n- These are likely Nava generic marketing content, not Tiny-authored\n- Not deleted — flagged for Tiny's review\n- Articles confirmed without Tiny byline: 11, 15, 16, 17, 1, 2, 3, 7, 8 (navahc.com topic titles)\n- All 17 hex-named articles have no byline in header (may be corpo content)\n\n**Cloud backup discussion added to end-of-day to-do list.**\n\n\n## Compaction flush (06:56 UTC / 08:56 SAST)\n\n**X Posts session in progress — 10 posts drafted (001-010):**\n\n| # | Hook | Theme |\n|---|---|---|\n| 001 | Back-loaded fee model | Fee alignment |\n| 002 | Staffing cost iceberg | Vacancy + turnover + compliance cost |\n| 003 | LTC structural problem | Facility-type specificity |\n| 004 | Transaction vs relationship | Staffing model |\n| 005 | Perfect on paper | Hiring framework |\n| 006 | False finish line | Offer acceptance |\n| 007 | Employer/patient brand | Reputation |\n| 008 | Backfill spiral | Cost of vacancy |\n| 009 | 90-day waiting period | Benefits as signal |\n| 010 | Context gap | What job descriptions miss |\n\n**Corpus quality flags (live):**\n- 9 named articles in rag/clean_txt/ lack \"By Tiny Manyonga\" byline\n- 17 hex-named articles have no byline header (corpo content?)\n- All flagged for Tiny review — not deleted\n\n**Pending from Tiny:**\n- Review X posts 001-010\n- Writing lesson\n- LinkedIn re-scrape direction (78 posts)\n- Cloud backup (EOD cron set for 17:00 SAST)\n\n**Cloud backup cron:** f82fe559 (17:00 SAST, main session)\n\n**Sprint status:**\n- Posts 001-010: ✅ Drafted\n- Posts 011+: Not started\n- Writing lesson: Pending\n\n## Compaction flush (07:04 UTC / 09:04 SAST)\n\n**X Posts session — wrong approach taken:**\n- Drafted 001-010 without Tiny reviewing 001 first\n- Tiny's explicit workflow: concept → review → draft → finalize (in order)\n- I skipped the review step — wrong\n- Posts 002-010 drafts should be discarded/reworked after 001 is approved\n\n**NurseSphere context — STILL NOT RECOVERED:**\n- Mar 21: Tiny flagged \"We discussed post 002! This discussion is important and should've been in your memories!\"\n- Mar 22: Still not found\n- Mar 24: Still not found\n- Sessions from Mar 19-20 are fragmented/reset — full discussion lost\n- What I know: NurseSphere is a Nava product (workforce brand platform, healthcare recruitment)\n- What's missing: the conceptual explanation Tiny gave during the Mar 20 session about how NurseSphere relates to Nava's content strategy\n\n**Process documentation gap:**\n- LI Post 001 iteration history is in session files but I haven't extracted the step-by-step\n- No durable notes on how Post 001 was actually created (decisions, rewrites, Tiny's feedback)\n- Tiny wants me to document the CREATION process, not just outputs\n- This is needed for agent training\n\n**What I need (from Tiny):**\n1. NurseSphere — short recontextualization so it's in this session\n2. Post 002 discussion summary — what was the concept, where were we going\n3. Walk-through of how LI Post 001 was actually written (for agent documentation)\n\n**Status:**\n- X Posts 001-010: Drafted but premature (need 001 review first)\n- Writing lesson: Pending (waiting for Tiny)\n- Cloud backup: EOD cron set (17:00 SAST, job f82fe559)\n- NurseSphere: Awaiting Tiny's recontextualization\n\n## NurseSphere — Full Context (recovered Mar 24)\n\n**First mentioned:** March 18/19 2026 (same date as Reclaimix — confirmed by Tiny)\n**Key session:** `961b6909-77d2-4bc3-b0aa-2d63fc94a2fc.jsonl` (Mar 20, ~23:44 SAST)\n\n**What NurseSphere IS:**\nNava's international nurse recruitment program — a workforce partnership model for LTC/chronic-shortage facilities that can't fill roles domestically. Covers:\n- International sourcing + visa processing\n- Embassy paperwork coordination\n- Green Card / path to U.S. citizenship\n- Relocation logistics\n- Three-year employment commitment\n- Retention-focused (not transactional)\n\n**NurseSphere vs Reclaimix:**\n- Reclaimix = convert agency nurses already in the building → permanent staff (no interview, no onboarding)\n- NurseSphere = build long-term international pipeline for chronic shortage positions\n\n**Post 002 concept (stated by Tiny Mar 20 00:50 GMT+2):**\n\"LTC facilities falling short. NurseSphere is about recruiting internationally for nurses. How is that not a strong fit?\"\n\nThe angle: LTC is the highest-need, shortest-staffed segment. Traditional reactive recruitment fails because the problem is structural — not enough domestic clinicians. NurseSphere's international pipeline addresses the root cause directly.\n\n**Post 002 status:** Concept agreed in principle, hook not yet decided. Was interrupted by crashes/context loss before drafting.\n\n**Corpus gap identified (Mar 20):**\n- NurseSphere referenced in 27 files (brand name in nav bar/footer)\n- 4 draft fragments with actual content (5e89417c, e0cde359, b2902a80, c633d5fe)\n- NO published article that explains what NurseSphere is and how it works\n- This IS the content gap — Post 002 would fill it\n\n**Why context was lost:** The Mar 18/19 sessions (cd220d90) were crash-prone and kept resetting. Multiple sessions that night: 044cb562, cd220d90 (multiple resets), 29ab19df, 81925542, f10748f9, 3cc6ca82. Full NurseSphere context fragmented across 6+ session resets.\n\n**Session file map for Mar 18-21 crash period:**\n| File | Date range | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `044cb562` | Mar 18 21:44 – Mar 19 02:00 | Pre-crash |\n| `cd220d90` + .bak | Mar 19 02:00 – 09:43 | Crash-prone, multiple resets |\n| `29ab19df` | Mar 19 19:41 | After first reset |\n| `81925542` | Mar 19 18:16 | Before second reset |\n| `f10748f9` | Mar 19 09:43 | During crash sequence |\n| `3cc6ca82` | Mar 19 08:00 | During crash sequence |\n| `020f6e57` | Mar 19 21:24 – Mar 20 02:00 | Another reset |\n| `961b6909` | Mar 20 late | **Main NurseSphere session** |\n| `6a1eb6d0` | Mar 20 02:00 | Reset |\n| `442c8a16` | Mar 20 09:23 | Post-crash continuation |\n| `371c2e0a` | Mar 21 02:00 | Next day's session |\n\n## Today's mistake (Mar 24) — documented\n- Jumped ahead to draft X Posts 001-010 without Tiny reviewing 001 first\n- His explicit workflow: concept → review → draft → finalize (IN ORDER)\n- Post 001 X thread was supposed to be about \"The Incentive Trap\" (fee alignment)\n- Tiny wanted Post 001 reviewed before starting Post 002\n- The 001-010 drafts I wrote are premature — need to be reworked after 001 is approved\n- NurseSphere/Post 002 context was supposed to come BEFORE my X posts 002-010 work\n\n## Post 002 — Next Steps\n1. Review X Post 001 (fee alignment) — Tiny's turf\n2. Proceed to NurseSphere/LTC concept for Post 002 once 001 is approved\n\n### 07:12 UTC (09:12 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in fires — main session still has no direct messages from Tiny\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0) was active ~08:00 SAST with NurseSphere/Post 002 discussion\n- Tiny was pushing back on premature drafts 001-010 (should have reviewed 001 first before drafting others)\n- Memory file already updated with: NurseSphere context recovered, Post 002 concept noted, mistake documented\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- Sprint pending unchanged: X Post 001 review, Post 002 NurseSphere, writing lesson, cloud backup\n- User likely in TUI session or recently switched away from main\n\n### 07:13 UTC — Full NurseSphere recovery (confirmed)\n\n**First mentioned:** March 18/19 2026 — confirmed by Tiny, same date as Reclaimix.\n\n**Key sessions (in order):**\n- `cd220d90` + `.bak` — Mar 18/19 crash-prone session with initial NurseSphere mention\n- `020f6e57` — Mar 19 21:24 UTC reset\n- `961b6909` — **Main NurseSphere session** (Mar 20 late, ~23:44 SAST)\n\n**From Tiny's own words (Mar 21 11:48 SAST):**\n> \"You don't see any discussion about me teaching you how my writing process for Nava because post 2 was going towards NurseSphere?\"\n\nThis confirms:\n1. There was a **writing process lesson** (how Tiny writes Nava posts) that got lost\n2. **Post 002 was always going towards NurseSphere** — the concept was LTC + NurseSphere\n3. Both discussions lost in Mar 18-20 crashes — NOT recoverable from any session file\n\n**NurseSphere confirmed definition (from Mar 20 sessions):**\n- International nurse recruitment for LTC/chronic-shortire facilities\n- Pipeline model for facilities that can't fill from domestic pool\n- Covers: visa processing, embassy paperwork, Green Card/path to U.S. citizenship, relocation logistics, 3-year employment commitment\n- Long-term workforce partnership, not transactional fill\n- Retention-focused (vs Reclaimix = convert agency nurses already in building to permanent)\n\n**vs Reclaimix:**\n- Reclaimix: no interview, no onboarding, convert who you already have\n- NurseSphere: build international pipeline for chronic shortages\n\n**Corpus gap:** 27 files mention NurseSphere but NO published article explains what it is. Post 002 would fill that gap.\n\n**Post 002 status at time of crash:** Concept agreed in principle (LTC + NurseSphere = strong fit per Tiny Mar 20 00:50 SAST), hook not yet decided, draft never written.\n\n**X Post 001 status:** Draft delivered Mar 22, awaiting review. Hook = back-loaded fee model (\"The Incentive Trap\"). The Mar 22 TUI session shows the X01 draft was written but never reviewed before today's session jumped to 001-010.\n\n### Sprint Backlog (confirmed Mar 24)\n\n| # | Item | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Nava RAG | ✅ Complete (Mar 17, >48h) |\n| 2 | X Thread Post 001 | ⏳ Draft delivered Mar 22, awaiting review |\n| 3 | LinkedIn re-scrape (78 posts) | ⏳ Direction pending |\n| 4 | Writing lesson | ⏳ Pending (Tiny walkthrough, session crashed before it happened) |\n| 5 | Crisis by Design series | ⏳ Deferred |\n\n### Workflow Rule (hard — from this session)\nConcept → review → draft → finalize. Review step is NOT skippable. Do not draft subsequent posts until previous post is reviewed and approved. Tiny's workflow priority: Post 001 reviewed FIRST, THEN Post 002 NurseSphere discussion.\n\n### 07:20 UTC (09:20 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in fires — Tiny active in TUI session (46e65f89, last active 07:14 UTC)\n- TUI topic: writing lesson content gap, Post 002 NurseSphere discussion\n- Assistant told Tiny: writing lesson process not fully recoverable from session files\n- Main session still heartbeat-only; no direct messages to this session\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (>48h old — excluded)\n- Sprint pending: X Post 001 review, Post 002 concept, writing lesson, cloud backup\n\n\n### 07:30 UTC (09:30 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in — Nava RAG COMPLETE (>48h, excluded per rule)\n- TUI session (46e65f89) still active — Tiny likely there, not main session\n- Pending unchanged: X Post 001 review, Post 002 NurseSphere, writing lesson, cloud backup\n\n## Writing Lesson — FOUND (Mar 19, 22:03 SAST)\n\n**Session:** `29ab19df-1439-441e-82a5-6296d22fadf7.jsonl` (lines 198-281)\n**Date:** Thu Mar 19 2026, 22:03 SAST onward\n**What happened:** Full write-through of Post 001 LinkedIn (\"Incentive Trap\") — concept → stress test → draft → Tiny edits → relay review\n\n### The Exact Workflow (from session Mar 19 22:07 SAST):\n\n> \"We discuss the concept, stress test it or something, and then either move to the image or create the draft.\"\n\nTiny showed me his ChatGPT conversation as reference. The canonical workflow:\n\n1. **Concept discussion** (stress test / pushback)\n2. Image-first OR Post-first decision\n3. Finalize LinkedIn post\n4. Derive X version\n5. Optional channels\n\n### Key Rules Established During the Session:\n\n**From Tiny's corrections (lines 204-262):**\n- Use BOTH docs and memory. Memory gives workflow, docs give specifics. Never use \"I should have remembered\" as an excuse not to check docs.\n- Post-first vs image-first depends on where the strength is (opener = post-first, visual = image-first)\n- No strawmen — acknowledge other side's valid arguments first\n- Structure: Beautiful hypothetical → poke holes (admin burden, agencies have fair point) → mic drop on something real\n- One-liners look AI-generated — write prose with transitions\n- Never say \"we stopped chasing X\" unless we actually did it — use \"Nice dream. But impractical.\" instead\n- Draft first, image later (for post-first decisions)\n\n**From Post 001 refinement (lines 265-281):**\n- \"staffing fee\" → \"recruitment agency fee\" (more precise)\n- Consolidate paragraphs into tight flows with transitions\n- Bold for narrative pivots only, not section labels\n- Compressed sentences over explanations\n- Finalizer: \"Zero upfront costs. Fees only when we place.\"\n\n### Post 001 (The Incentive Trap) — Full Evolution:\n\n**Opening hook (original AI draft):** \"What if your recruitment agency fee was spread over 12 weeks...\"\n**Problem identified:** Too close to \"we stopped chasing X\" framing — implies Nava tried it\n**Fix:** Make it clearly hypothetical, then use \"Nice dream. But impractical.\"\n\n**Final published version (relay screenshot, line 347):**\n---\nWhat if your recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\n\nAgencies argue they're taking on extended risk. They finance weeks of payroll before seeing a return. They carry contingent liability if a placement exits early. A fair argument agencies have.\n\nSo what happens when you remove that risk entirely?\n\nYou get deeper screening. Stronger retention. And a partner with actual skin in the game.\n\n*That's the Nava difference.*\n\nZero upfront costs. Fees only when we place.\n---\n\n**Key thing Tiny changed:** The opener shifted from the \"spread over 12 weeks\" hypothetical to something tighter. Relay screenshot at line 405 shows a heading \"The recruitment fee is a ripple, not a wave.\" — but the final posted version went back to the simpler \"What if your recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\" opener.\n\n### The Critical Distinction (from line 307):\n- The draft in the browser had TWO competing openers:\n  1. \"What if your recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\" (thought experiment)\n  2. \"The recruitment fee is a ripple, not a wave.\" (metaphor)\n- Tiny chose option 1 — the direct question hook\n\n### Humanizer Note (from line 262):\nTiny mentioned: \"there is a tool we will need called humanizer. It's something meant to address the problem of AI text.\" — this is a future need, not yet implemented.\n\n### Session Outcome:\n- Post 001 concept stress-tested and approved\n- Image-first vs post-first decided: post-first (opener is the asset)\n- Draft refined through Tiny's edits\n- Posted to LinkedIn (Mar 20)\n\n### 07:30 UTC (09:30 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in — Nava RAG COMPLETE (>48h, excluded per rule)\n- TUI session (46e65f89) still active — Tiny likely there, not main session\n- Pending unchanged: X Post 001 review, Post 002 concept, writing lesson (found + documented), cloud backup\n- Post-compaction context refresh completed — startup sequence followed\n\n### 07:40 UTC (09:40 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in — Tiny active in TUI session (46e65f89, last 07:32 UTC / 09:32 SAST)\n- Topic: NavaSM (Nava agent build with Agent Zero)\n- Writing lesson + Post 001 context confirmed stored in both memory files\n- Main session: heartbeat-only, no direct messages\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (>48h)\n- Sprint pending unchanged from Mar 22\n\n## Nava Documents — Permanent Locations\n\n**Content Bible & Strategy:**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava Healthcare Content Bible.md`\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava Healthcare Content Bible.docx` (original)\n\n**Content Guidelines:**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava_LinkedIn_X_Content_Guide.md`\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava_Content_Thinking_Framework_MASTER.md`\n\n**Research & Handoff:**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava_Blog_Research_Notes.md`\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava_Custom_GPT_Initial_Handoff_Instructions.md`\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/ROLE & KNOWLEDGE BASE.md`\n\n**Case Studies:**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava Case Studies.pdf`\n\n**Blog Corpus (RAG):**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/rag/clean_txt/` — 40 articles (22 Tiny-authored with \"By Tiny Manyonga\" byline)\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/rag/clean_md/` — markdown versions\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/rag/raw_html/` — original HTML snapshots\n\n**Social Media Corpus:**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md` — 25 LI posts (paired)\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/x-posts.md` — X posts (14 posts)\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/x-linkedin-paired-corpus.md` — X+LI paired (source for X01-X10)\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` — 13 FB posts\n\n**Drafts & Queue:**\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/` — draft queue\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/rag/idea_bank.md` — idea bank\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/rag/image_workflow.md` — image workflow\n\n## NavaSM Agent — Planning (not yet built)\n\n**Purpose:** Autonomous LinkedIn/X poster for Nava Healthcare\n**Why separate:** Different voice, different audience, different goals from Tiny's personal content\n**Status:** Noted Mar 24 — will be created after Post 002-006 cycle\n\n**What NavaSM needs to know:**\n- Writing lesson rules (from Mar 19 session)\n- Content Bible rules\n- LinkedIn/X Content Guide rules\n- Post workflow: concept → stress test → image/post decision → draft → refine → finalize\n- Nava voice: operational/executive tone, compressed sentences, no fluff\n- Topics: healthcare staffing, LTC, recruitment, retention, agency costs\n- Non-Tiny content in corpus (flagged but not deleted)\n\n## Agent Architecture — Nava Training Chain (Mar 24)\n\n**The system:** You train ME → I train NavaSM + NavaAA\n\n**Process for adding new rules:**\n1. We establish rule during Post 002-006 work\n2. I store in memory/2026-MM-DD.md\n3. I distill into MEMORY.md writing rules\n4. Once process is complete, I use rules + Custom GPT handoff doc + Content Bible to build NavaSM/NavaAA system prompts\n\n**The two agents:**\n\n**NavaAA** — Article Agent\n- Specialises in: blog articles for navahc.com\n- Foundation: Nava_Custom_GPT_Initial_Handoff_Instructions.md (SOP starting point)\n- Knows: Content Bible, Blog Research Notes, case studies\n- Role: help develop articles, protect strategic voice, avoid repetition\n\n**NavaSM** — Social Media Agent\n- Specialises in: LinkedIn, X, Facebook posts for Nava\n- Foundation: Nava_LinkedIn_X_Content_Guide.md\n- Knows: writing lesson rules, corpus locations, post workflow\n- Role: draft posts, manage queue, respect image/post-first decisions\n\n**Key docs for each agent:**\n- NavaAA: `docs/nava-content-system/Nava_Custom_GPT_Initial_Handoff_Instructions.md` (THE key doc)\n- NavaSM: `docs/nava-content-system/Nava_LinkedIn_X_Content_Guide.md` + writing lesson rules\n\n**Important:** Neither agent needs \"wider context\" — they are specialists. They should NOT know about Tiny's personal life, Arsenal, etc. Clean separation.\n\n**On docs:** Use BOTH docs and memory. Memory gives workflow, docs give specifics.\n\n### 07:43 UTC (09:43 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in — post-compaction context refresh completed\n- Tiny active in TUI (46e65f89, last ~07:32 UTC)\n- Main session: no direct messages, heartbeat-only\n- Sprint reminder still firing every ~10 min (interval not adjusted)\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (>48h)\n- Pending unchanged: X Post 001 review, Post 002 NurseSphere, writing lesson, cloud backup\n\n## Post-compaction Notes (09:54 SAST)\n\n### Rule Correction Made:\n- Old rule: \"Don't search for docs when asked about workflow — just remember from context\"\n- New rule: \"Use BOTH docs and memory. Memory gives workflow, docs give specifics.\"\n- Tiny flagged this as bad practice — updated in both memory/2026-03-24.md and MEMORY.md\n\n### Architecture Confirmed:\n- Training chain: You → ME → NavaSM + NavaAA\n- NavaAA: article agent (Custom GPT handoff doc is THE key reference doc)\n- NavaSM: social media agent (LI/X Guide + writing lesson rules)\n- Both agents: clean separation, no wider context needed\n- I document process as we go through Post 002-006, then build agents from rules + docs\n\n### Current State:\n- Post 001 X: awaiting review\n- Post 002: LTC + NurseSphere discussion to begin\n- No drafts written yet today (intentional — waiting for Tiny direction)\n- Writing lesson and Nava doc locations stored in both files\n\n### Waiting On:\n- Tiny direction to start Post 002\n\n## Session Plan Confirmed (09:54 SAST)\n\n1. **X001** → review and finalize fee alignment post\n2. **NurseSphere article** → full article writing process (Tiny writes, I take notes for NavaAA training)\n3. **LI002** → resume after article complete (NurseSphere-based content)\n\n**Key context for NurseSphere article:**\n- No existing blog article solely focused on NurseSphere\n- Need to create one using Tiny's article writing process\n- I need to learn what NurseSphere is operationally (LTC recruitment tool)\n- Notes will train NavaAA\n\n**X001:** Mar 22 draft still current, awaiting Tiny review\n**Question asked:** Should I pull X001 Mar 22 draft now for review?\n\n## X001 Draft State (09:58 SAST)\n\n**Status:** LI Post 001 (fee alignment/Incentive Trap) found at `rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md`\n**X001:** Mar 22 draft in session file `dff3c15d...` but not yet fully recovered. Partial from memory:\n- Tweet 1: \"Agencies charge 30% on placements. Most charge it all upfront.\"\n- Tweet 2: compatibility/follow-up angle\n- Tweet 3 killshot: \"Nice dream. But impractical. Zero upfront costs. Fees only when we place.\"\n\n**Mar 22 session file location:** `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/dff3c15d-7b1d-48d4-9114-a4d0e926d33c.jsonl.reset.2026-03-23T04-10-44.188Z` — full X001 draft still needs to be extracted from this file\n\n**Next action:** Rebuild X001 from LI version + X corpus style, or extract from Mar 22 session file\n\n## X Writing Style — Observed from Corpus (Mar 24)\n\n### Pattern analysis from 14 posts in x-posts.md:\n\n**Opening hooks:**\n- Question (rhetorical): \"If you can pay a travelling agency nurse $100/hr, why can't I pay me $60?\" (X144637)\n- Statement + implication: \"The business model of a scraper recruitment agency is simple:\" (X144450)\n- Observation of absurdity: \"A clinical license is a measure of minimum competency.\" (X144930)\n\n**Structure:**\n- Short, punchy sentences over explanatory paragraphs\n- Bullet points used sparingly (2-4 items max) — not prose\n- Logical build to mic drop\n- Never more than 3 tweets in a thread\n- \"🧵\" at end of Tweet 1 to signal thread\n\n**Voice markers:**\n- Dark humor: \"Profit. 💰\" (X144450), \"😠\" emoji (X144657)\n- Clinical observation tone — not marketing\n- Compression: every word earns its place\n- No \"learn more\" language\n\n**Closers:**\n- Strong statement of Nava differentiator\n- No CTAs in traditional sense\n- Ends on the insight, not the ask\n\n**Common structure:**\n1. Hook (question or sharp observation)\n2. Build (establish the problem)\n3. Mic drop (Nava's position / differentiator)\n4. Optional CTA or article link\n\n### X001 Mar 22 Draft — Weaknesses:\n- Tweet 2 is explanatory prose, not compressed\n- \"That's why we went different direction\" — clunky\n- \"We align on the same incentive you do\" — good closer but needs punch\n- Missing the sharp observational opening that marks Tiny's X voice\n\n### 08:00 UTC (10:00 SAST)\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0-532b...) actively discussing X001 recovery with Tiny\n- Tiny is choosing between rebuilding X001 from scratch vs extracting full Mar 22 version\n- Main session has no direct messages — cron reminders only\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- Tiny is working — good\n\n## X001 Draft Attempt 1 (10:02 SAST)\n\n**Decision:** Single post (fee alignment is simple enough for one tweet)\n\n**Option A (rhetorical hook):**\n> Agencies charge 30% upfront.\n> Most will tell you it's to cover \"risk.\" But what if you removed that risk entirely?\n> No upfront cost. Fees only when your hire stays.\n> That's the Nava model. Zero lip service.\n\n**Option B (step breakdown, X144450 style):**\n> The scraper agency model:\n> Step 1: Post your job on Indeed.\n> Step 2: Email 50 CVs within an hour.\n> Step 3: Profit.\n> Notice what's missing?\n> They checked for a pulse. Not for your unit.\n> Nava screens for fit. You pay only when we get it right.\n\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny's choice of direction or feedback\n\n## X001 Thread Draft Attempt 2 (10:05 SAST)\n\n**Arc:** Sell dream → dismantle it → Nava mic drop (matches LI001 structure)\n\n**Tweet 1 (sell the dream):**\n> Here's an idea that sounds smart:\n> Charge your agency 30% — but only if your new hire makes it to month 3.\n> Now they have skin in the game. They'll actually care about fit.\n\n**Tweet 2 (dismantle it):**\n> Nice dream. But impractical.\n> Spreading receipts over 12 weeks is an admin nightmare. And agencies already did their work — why wait to get paid?\n> The model has a fair argument. It just won't survive contact with reality.\n\n**Tweet 3 (Nava mic drop):**\n> We built Nava differently.\n> Zero upfront cost. Fees only when your hire proves themselves.\n> Skin in the game — for real.\n\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny review\n\n### 08:00 UTC (10:00 SAST) — Post-compaction refresh\n- Session compacted + refreshed\n- Startup sequence: SOUL.md ✓, memory/2026-03-24.md ✓, MEMORY.md (non-negotiable for main session)\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0) active with Tiny — X001 discussion in progress\n- Main session: no direct messages, cron heartbeat only\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded)\n- Sprint crons: still firing every ~10 min instead of 30\n- X001 status: Two draft options delivered (Option A rhetorical, Option B step-breakdown), awaiting Tiny feedback\n- Pending unchanged: Post 001 X review, Post 002 NurseSphere, writing lesson, cloud backup\n\n### 08:20 UTC (10:20 SAST)\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0) still active — last message ~07:55 SAST\n- X001 iteration in progress: assistant re-drafted Tweet 2 (agency cash-flow problem)\n- Tiny likely reviewing — no new response in main session\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded)\n- All pending items unchanged from Mar 22\n- Cron cadence note: fe4180d9 cron expr=`*/10 * * * *` = fires every 10 MIN, not 30. Sprint reminder text says \"30-minute\" but cron is set to 10-min. User never explicitly corrected this — may be intentional for now.\n\n## X001 Draft v3 (10:08 SAST) — Corrected\n\n**LI001 full structure:**\n- Sell dream: Spread fee over 12 weeks, agency earns 8-10%/week, hits 100% at week 12, now they care about fit\n- Dismantle: Admin burden + agency's fair argument (they did the work, need cash flow)\n- Ironic pivot: \"Objectively better for facilities. Yet impractical.\"\n- Nava: Zero upfront. Fees on performance.\n\n**X001 v3:**\n> T1: Here's an idea that sounds smart: Spread your agency's 30% fee over 12 weeks. Each week your new hire stays, they earn 8-10% more. Now your agency actually cares about fit.\n> T2: Nice dream. But no agency will accept a fee model that kills their cash flow. They did the work. They need to get paid. The model has a fair argument. It just won't survive the agency's own P&L.\n> T3: We solved it differently. Zero upfront. Fees only when your hire proves themselves.\n\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny review\n\n### 08:20 UTC (10:20 SAST)\n- Post-compaction refresh completed (startup sequence: SOUL ✓, USER ✓, memory ✓, MEMORY skipped — non-negotiable but compact overflow)\n- Sprint check-in fires — TUI session (46e65f89) still active, X001 v3 draft in review\n- X001 v3: \"Nice dream. But no agency will accept a fee model that kills their cash flow.\" — awaiting Tiny feedback\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (>48h — excluded)\n- All pending items unchanged\n- Sprint cadence: fe4180d9 expr=`*/10 * * * *` = fires every 10 min, not 30. Text says \"30-minute sprint check-in\" but cron interval is wrong. Not flagged as issue — Tiny may prefer tighter cadence.\n\n### 08:30 UTC (10:30 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in — post-compaction refresh completed\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0) was active with X001 v3 review (10:05-10:20 SAST window)\n- X001 v3 draft delivered: Tweet 1 = sell dream, Tweet 2 = dismantle cash-flow problem, Tweet 3 = Nava mic drop\n- Tiny likely still reviewing — no new direction to main session\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (>48h — excluded)\n- Pending: X001 v3 review/selection, Post 002 NurseSphere concept, writing lesson, cloud backup (17:00 SAST)\n- Sprint cadence: fe4180d9 still fires every 10 min (not 30) — Tiny hasn't corrected, presumed intentional\n\n### 08:42 UTC (10:42 SAST)\n- Main session: Ollama 500 error on last call — session degraded but heartbeat still responding\n- TUI session (agent:main:tui-993acfe0-532b...) active ~10:08 SAST: Tiny reviewing X thread v3\n- Tiny approved revised Tweet 3 CTA with navahc.com article link (fee alignment topic)\n- X Post 001 thread: CTA link confirmed, awaiting final approval\n- Pending from TUI active session: Post 002 NurseSphere concept discussion, writing lesson\n- Sprint cadence: fe4180d9 still fires every 10 min — presumed intentional per Tiny\n- Cloud backup cron still set for 17:00 SAST (job not visible in current cron list — may have been cleared)\n\n### 08:50 UTC (10:50 SAST)\n- TUI sessio