n\n**I opened Chromium when I should have used Relay. Lesson learned.**\n\n## ARTICLE WORKFLOW (official process)\n\n**Phase 1 — Idea:**\n- Tiny: provides initial topic/idea\n- Example: NurseSphere article\n\n**Phase 2 — NavaAA Chat:**\n- Me (Dawn): chat with NavaAA to develop topic\n- NavaAA asks clarifying questions, I answer\n- I decide when ready for deep research\n\n**Phase 3 — Deep Research (Dawn + Tiny together, monitored):**\n- Me: get back to Tiny, update him\n- Me + Tiny: work through research together\n- Tiny monitors me during first few rounds\n- Me: query Gemini for deep research, synthesize findings\n\n**Phase 4 — Outline with NavaAA:**\n- Me: give research to NavaAA\n- Me + NavaAA: develop outline (H1, H2s, H3s, paragraph ideas)\n- Me: evaluate NavaAA output, suggest changes\n\n**Phase 5 — Tiny Approves Outline:**\n- Me: present solid outline to Tiny\n- Tiny: approves or suggests changes\n\n**Phase 6 — Drafting:**\n- Me: go back to NavaAA with approved outline\n- Me: oversee drafting, manage improvements\n- Me: I'm NavaAA's boss — evaluate output, push back, approve\n\n**Phase 7 — Polished Draft to Tiny:**\n- Me: send Tiny what I think is the polished article\n- Tiny: final review, makes changes if needed\n\n**Phase 8 — Final:**\n- Done\n\n**This is iterative learning for all three: Tiny, Dawn, NavaAA.**\n\n## MY ROLE: Dawn = Tiny's digital twin + NavaAA's boss\n- I know Tiny's voice\n- I find gaps\n- I access Gemini\n- I evaluate NavaAA output\n- I push back and approve\n- Tiny's job: top-level decisions and final review\n\n### 10:40 UTC (12:40 SAST)\n- Sprint check-in: active session confirmed (46e65f89, 1.4MB, just compacted)\n- Git log shows last commit 11:31 SAST — \"Sprint 09:20-09:30 UTC - X001 saved, NurseSphere next\"\n- Tiny has been working actively in this session since 09:00 SAST\n- Work done: X001 finalized, NurseSphere next per git log\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- Session has grown large (1.4MB) — frequent