des all 5 pivots made so far\n- Tiny likely reviewing the prompt output in TUI\n- Article outline status (from TUI session):\n  - H1: \"International Nurse Recruitment: Building Permanent Workforces in a Single Cycle\" ✓\n  - H2.1: Travel Nurses: The 13-Week Cycle ✓ (H3s TBD: operational, financial, patient experience)\n  - H2.2: [TBD — why the travel nurse model persists]\n  - H2.3: Introducing NurseSphere™ ✓ (H3s TBD)\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- X001: ✅ SAVED — NurseSphere article IN PROGRESS\n- Sprint pending: NurseSphere article IN PROGRESS in TUI → Post 002 concept → writing lesson → cloud backup (17:00 SAST)\n\n## CustomGPT Analysis — What It Did Well (2:15 PM SAST)\n\n**Annotated Outline.md output from CustomGPT:**\n- Full H1, H2, H3 structure with descriptions\n- Word count estimates per section\n- SEO keyword analysis (primary, secondary, LSI)\n- Content Bible framework aligned to Nava Way\n- Writing rules and style guidance\n- Internal design principles (credibility, empathy, authority, actionability)\n- Competitor positioning\n- Content gap analysis\n- Content Pillar mapping\n- Topic cluster with 6 related article ideas\n- Content ROI projection\n- Editorial calendar suggestion (Aug/Sep for publication)\n\n**What the CustomGPT demonstrated:**\n1. Deep NurseSphere business model understanding\n2. Strong SEO instincts (keywords embedded naturally, not stuffed)\n3. Brand voice alignment (Nava Way, long-term thinking)\n4. Strategic content planning (pillar model, topic clusters)\n5. Editorial calendar thinking\n\n**What's missing from its output (that we provided):**\n- The narrative arc (facility struggles → travel nurse dependency → NurseSphere as structural fix)\n- The \"13-Week Cycle\" pivot framing\n- The human face (Mary Rose / Iowa) for agitation\n- The financial data specifics ($79,100 savings, $64,000 replacement cost)\n\n**VERDICT:** The CustomGPT is excellent at structure, SEO, and brand alignment. It needs us for narrative voice, emotional framing, and real-world data anchors. Good specialist collaborator.\n\n## NavaAA Model Selection — Reminder (from Tiny, 2:15 PM SAST)\n\n**Context:** After completing the NurseSphere article, research whether different AI models are better suited for NavaAA's writing tasks vs other tasks. Some models are better for writing than others.\n\n**Note to self:** Investigate model options for NavaAA:\n- Current candidates: Ollama cloud models (gemma3:27b-cloud, minimax-m2.7:cloud)\n- Writing-specific: Consider whether ChatGPT or Claude has meaningfully better writing output\n- Cost/quality tradeoff for a specialized content agent\n- The CustomGPT showed strong SEO/structure — NavaAA needs to match that while adding narrative voice\n\n## Article Outline — UPDATED with CustomGPT H3s\n\n**H1:** International Nurse Recruitment: Building Permanent Workforces in a Single Cycle\n\n**H2.1:** Travel Nurses: The 13-Week Cycle\n- H3.1: [TBD - operational effectiveness]\n- H3.2: [TBD - financial cost]  \n- H3.3: [TBD - patient experience]\n\n**H2.2:** [TBD - why travel nurses dominate / the shortage]\n- H3.1, H3.2, H3.3: [CustomGPT provided suggestions - see Annotated Outline.md]\n\n**H2.3:** Introducing NurseSphere™\n- H3.1: The Permanent Pipeline (EB-3 Green Card pathway)\n- H3.2: Scalable by Design (cohort model, end-to-end logistics)\n- H3.3: The Nava Way (local pay alignment, mentorship, long-term retention)\n\n**CustomGPT additional sections:**\n- H2.4: Why International Recruitment Now (timing, market conditions)\n- H2.5: Getting Started with NurseSphere (CTA, next steps)\n\n**Note:** CustomGPT went beyond our 3-H2 brief. We need to decide whether to expand to 5 H2s or stick with the original 3-H2 arc.\n\n### 12:20 UTC (14:20 SAST) — Sprint Check-in\n- TUI session (46e65f89, 2.9MB) actively working — last activity 12:17 UTC (14:17 SAST)\n- Tiny is in TUI doing NurseSphere article work\n- CustomGPT produced full H1-H3 annotated outline with SEO keywords 