{"type":"message","id":"c04ad821","parentId":"902b331a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T21:05:53.545Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_7f1c0353-78e1-4856-b4e8-081ec5a933ae","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nplatform: X (Twitter)\nauthor: Nava Healthcare Recruitment\ndate: 2026-03-24\nstatus: final_approved\ntype: thread\nimage: none\ncta: https://navahc.com/how-to-find-the-best-medical-recruiting-agencies/\nsource: X001_final\n---\n\n💡 Here is an idea that sounds smart for hiring healthcare facilities: \n\n📉 Spread the recruitment agency fee over 12 weeks. \n\nEach week your new hire stays, the agency earns an additional 8–10% of their fee. Now your agency 𝘢𝘤𝘵𝘶𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘺 cares about 𝗰𝘂𝗹𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗮𝗹 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 𝗳𝗶𝘁 because early resignation is lost money! 😃🤝\n\n--------------------------------------------\n\nNo, wait... Hold on, nice dream🤡\n\nNo agency will accept a fee model that complicates their cash flow while taking on extra risk. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝗱𝗶𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗴𝗲𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝗶𝗱. 💰💵🤑\n\nAlso, think about it, isn't this extra admin for your already busy HR department?\n\n------------------------------------------------------\n\n✨ We solved it differently. 𝗭𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝘂𝗽𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗻𝘁 𝗳𝗲𝗲𝘀! \n\nWe only get paid once the hire proves they belong. That's real skin in the game. 🤝 🎯\n\nHere's what to actually look for in a medical recruiting agency: https://navahc.com/how-to-find-the-best-medical-recruiting-agencies/"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"---\nplatform: X (Twitter)\nauthor: Nava Healthcare Recruitment\ndate: 2026-03-24\nstatus: final_approved\ntype: thread\nimage: none\ncta: https://navahc.com/how-to-find-the-best-medical-recruiting-agencies/\nsource: X001_final\n---\n\n💡 Here is an idea that sounds smart for hiring healthcare facilities: \n\n📉 Spread the recruitment agency fee over 12 weeks. \n\nEach week your new hire stays, the agency earns an additional 8–10% of their fee. Now your agency 𝘢𝘤𝘵𝘶𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘺 cares about 𝗰𝘂𝗹𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗮𝗹 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 𝗳𝗶𝘁 because early resignation is lost money! 😃🤝\n\n--------------------------------------------\n\nNo, wait... Hold on, nice dream🤡\n\nNo agency will accept a fee model that complicates their cash flow while taking on extra risk. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝗱𝗶𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗴𝗲𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝗶𝗱. 💰💵🤑\n\nAlso, think about it, isn't this extra admin for your already busy HR department?\n\n------------------------------------------------------\n\n✨ We solved it differently. 𝗭𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝘂𝗽𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗻𝘁 𝗳𝗲𝗲𝘀! \n\nWe only get paid once the hire proves they belong. That's real skin in the game. 🤝 🎯\n\nHere's what to actually look for in a medical recruiting agency: https://navahc.com/how-to-find-the-best-medical-recruiting-agencies/","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774386353543}}
